  "text": "The surfaces wettability was analyzed by the static sessile drop method. The contact angles of water droplets on the top face of the reference C (CVD) layer are 82.2 \u00b1 2.8\u00b0, respectively (Figure 2A ). The C (CVD) layer does not change the specificity of the surface with respect to the titanium substrate [CITATION_1] . The difference in the contact angles for C (CVD) incubated with Alb (78.4 \u00b1 2.3\u00b0) and HSA (84.5 \u00b1 1.9\u00b0) with comparison to a reference the C (CVD) layer is not so significant, it fits within the limit of 5% (Figure 2A) . However, the C (CVD) incubation in BSA leads to the creation of a film with hydrophobic characteristics and contact angle of 112.0 \u00b1 6.7\u00b0.",
